problem:
Two circles are centered at the origin, as shown.  The point $P(224,30)$ is on the larger circle and the point $S(0,k)$ is on the smaller circle.  If $QR=113$, what is the value of $k$? [asy]
defaultpen(linewidth(.7pt)+fontsize(10pt));
dotfactor=4;
draw(Circle((0,0),113)); draw(Circle((0,0),226));
dot((0,0)); dot((113,0)); dot((226,0)); dot((0,113)); dot((224,30));
draw((0,0)--(224,30));
label("$S (0,k)$",(0,7.5),W);
draw((229,0)--(0,0)--(0,229),Arrows(TeXHead));
draw((-229,0)--(0,0)--(0,-229));

label("$x$",(229,0),E); label("$y$",(0,229),N); label("$P(224,30)$",(224,30),NE);

label("$O$",(0,0),SW); label("$Q$",(113,0),SW); label("$R$",(226,0),SE);

[/asy]
